  "title": "Chinese Tutor",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Job Description:</strong></h3>\n<ol>\n  <li>Provide one-on-one instruction in Chinese language subjects, including language skills, writing, and reading comprehension.</li>\n  <li>Assist students in reinforcing school curriculum and preparing for exams such as midterms and finals.</li>\n  <li>Guide students in improving their language proficiency, reading comprehension, and writing techniques.</li>\n  <li>Plan and manage teaching schedules, and tailor materials and teaching methods based on each student’s progress. For example: setting weekly lesson plans and homework assignments.</li>\n  <li>Provide regular progress reports and learning feedback to parents. For example: organizing and grading midterm and final exams.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3><strong>Qualifications:</strong></h3>\n<ol>\n  <li>Educational background in Chinese Literature, Chinese Language, Education, or Teacher Training is preferred.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with Taiwanese elementary to high school curriculum, materials, and exam trends.</li>\n  <li>Experience as a school Chinese teacher, cram school instructor, or private tutor is highly preferred.</li>\n  <li>Ability to tailor instruction to different grade levels and student abilities.</li>\n  <li>Passionate about education, with patience and strong communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Mandarin teaching certification is a plus.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3><strong>Work Schedule:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>5 days per week</li>\n  <li>Daily hours: <strong>3:30 PM – 8:30 PM</strong>, with a 1-hour break included</li>\n</ul>",
